Parliament, Monday, 03 September 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs will tomorrow chart a way forward on the process it will follow, to commence with the inquiry on the process followed in the naturalisation of the Gupta family. The committee will also receive a briefing from the Minister of Home Affairs, senior management of the South African Police Service as well as the Chief of the Tshwane Metro police in relation to the security situation around the Desmond Tutu Refugee Office. The committee visited the office last week and raised concerns over security challenges around the office Details of the meeting
	Date: Tuesday, 04 September 2018
	Venue: V119, Old Assembly building
	Time: 09:30 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON HOME AFFAIRS, MR HLOMANI CHAUKE For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
